<%
  const breadcrumbs = [
    { name: "Home", href: "/" },
    { name: "About", href: "/about" }
  ];
%>

<%- include('partials/head', {
  title,
  metaTitle: 'About PNW Carriage Masters | Our Story',
  metaDescription: 'Learn how PNW Carriage Masters was founded by Andy and Paula White and how a classic ERF became the basis of a specialist truck hearse service across the UK.',
  canonicalPath: '/about',
  breadcrumbs
}) %>

<%- include('partials/header') %>

<%
  const s = settings || {};
  const phoneRaw = String(s.phone || "").trim();
  const phoneTel = phoneRaw.replace(/\s+/g, "");
%>

<div class="wrap">
  <%- include('partials/breadcrumbs', { breadcrumbs }) %>

  <div class="card">
    <h1 style="color: var(--accent);">About PNW Carriage Masters</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      PNW Carriage Masters is a family-run business, conceived in 2018 and operated by husband-and-wife team
      Andy and Paula White. It was created from a lifelong passion for trucks and a deep respect for the funeral profession.
    </p>

    <div class="cta" style="margin:18px 0 8px;">
      <a class="btn" href="/contact">Enquire</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/gallery">View gallery</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/case-studies">Case studies</a>
      <% if (phoneTel) { %>
        <a class="btn" href="tel:<%= phoneTel %>">Call <%= phoneRaw %></a>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">How it began</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        Andy had owned a classic ERF truck for around fifteen years. It is one of the last ERFs built at
        Sandbach, Cheshire, and in its day was a top-of-the-range model with numerous factory extras.
        Known as the <strong>Black Cat</strong> because of its colour and its Caterpillar C12 engine,
        it is a rare example, with very few ERFs produced in this specification.
      </p>
      <p>
        Alongside a long-standing interest in cars and trucks, Andy also held a genuine respect for the funeral profession.
        He shared with Paula his ambition to create a bespoke truck hearse that could offer families an alternative
        to the traditional car-based hearse.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">Building the first truck hearse</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        With Paula’s encouragement and support, work began on converting the ERF, with the help of Andy’s best friend,
        Peter Lewis. Peter brought more than forty years of experience in the haulage industry and was an accomplished mechanic
        as well as a Class 1 driver.
      </p>
      <p>
        Great care and attention were given to the design and detail of the hearse, with many subtle personal touches
        incorporated throughout. Andy, a lifelong Queen fan, felt that the closing line of
        <em>Bohemian Rhapsody</em> — <em>“Anyway the wind blows”</em> — perfectly summed up a trucker’s life.
        That sentiment now carries across the expanded fleet.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">A story with real meaning</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        During the build, Peter was sadly diagnosed with cancer, but he encouraged Andy to continue the project.
        The truck was eventually completed and went on to win first prize at a truck show.
      </p>
      <p>
        Peter remained closely involved and supportive until the end. After his passing, his family said there was
        only one way he would take his final journey — with Andy at the wheel.
      </p>
      <p>
        That experience only deepened the purpose behind PNW Carriage Masters: to offer families a truly unique,
        personal and meaningful send-off for loved ones who would have wanted a genuine HGV farewell.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">What PNW Carriage Masters offers today</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        Today, PNW Carriage Masters provides specialist truck hearse and lorry hearse hire across the UK mainland,
        working with the funeral profession to help families create a final journey that feels fitting, individual and memorable.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our vehicles are chosen not for novelty, but because they can reflect a lifetime connected to haulage,
        engineering, transport, recovery, mechanics or life on the road.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom:0;">
        You can explore our <a href="/gallery">gallery</a>, view recent <a href="/case-studies">case studies</a>,
        or read more about our <a href="/renault-magnum-hearse">Renault Magnum</a> and
        <a href="/erf-ec12-hearse">ERF EC12</a> hearses.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title">Related pages</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p><a href="/gallery">Gallery</a></p>
      <p><a href="/case-studies">Case studies</a></p>
      <p><a href="/renault-magnum-hearse">Renault Magnum truck hearse</a></p>
      <p><a href="/erf-ec12-hearse">ERF EC12 lorry hearse</a></p>
      <p><a href="/contact">Contact</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
